SENATE JOINT RESOLUTION 35
By Pody
A RESOLUTION to recognize Dr. Christopher E. Townson on the
occasion of his retirement.
WHEREAS, it is appropriate that the members of this General Assembly should honor
those citizens who have performed with uncommon devotion and enthusiasm throughout their
years of public service; and
WHEREAS, Dr. Christopher E. Townson is one such estimable individual, who, having
rendered more than eight years of service as chief executive officer (CEO) of DeKalb Telephone
Cooperative (DTC), Inc., will take his much-deserved retirement this year; and
WHEREAS, Dr. Townson began his fruitful career in the telecommunications industry as
an installer and repairman at Farmers Communication Cooperative in Rainsville, Alabama; he
rose through the ranks to management positions in 2002 and again in 2010; and
WHEREAS, with nearly three decades of leadership experience in the
telecommunications and broadcasting fields, Dr. Townson joined DTC in 2016 and led its
financial turnaround, ultimately bringing the company from negative net earnings to a flourishing
and valuable company with strong financial performance; and
WHEREAS, under his astute leadership, DTC saw a complete overhaul of its aging
infrastructure; DTC expanded its service area by more than 300 square miles and delivered
world-class fiber optic technology to its members, a project that stayed under budget and was
completed four years ahead of schedule; and
WHEREAS, in addition to his involvement at DTC, Dr. Townson has served as CEO of
Advantage Cellular Systems, Inc., and First Choice Security, Inc.; additionally, he founded
FourSight Communications, LLC, which brought broadband to underserved communities; and
