WHEREAS, Dr. Townson earned an Associate of Science degree in General Studies
from Northeast Alabama Community College in 1998; a Bachelor of Science degree in
Organizational Management from Covenant College in 2000; a Master of Business
Administration degree from the University of Alabama at Birmingham in 2006; and a Doctor of
Ministry degree in Organizational Leadership from the New Orleans Baptist Theological
Seminary in 2020; and
WHEREAS, throughout his estimable career, Dr. Christopher Townson has remained
committed to innovation and industry leadership, demonstrating the utmost professionalism,
ability, and integrity, and winning the unbridled respect and admiration of his colleagues and
community alike; now, therefore,
BE IT RESOLVED BY THE SENATE OF THE ONE HUNDRED FOURTEENTH
GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF TENNESSEE, THE HOUSE OF
REPRESENTATIVES CONCURRING, that we extend to Dr. Christopher E. Townson our
heartfelt wishes for a happy and fulfilling retirement and every continued success in his future
endeavors.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED, that an appropriate copy of this resolution be prepared
